lead_paragraph: By the time Jake Arrieta threw his first pitch on Tuesday night, the Chicago Cubs were already in control of Game 6. By the time the reigning Cy Young winner gave up his first hit, a leadoff double in the fourth, the Cubs led by seven.

headline.print_headline: Arrieta Keeps Indians in Check as Cubs Force Game 7
